		"description": "{html}<div><p>Hi all,</p>\n<p>I'm using TM on iPhone.</p>\n<p>I can successfully create a toolbar with:<br>\nTitanium.UI.currentWindow.setToolbar</p>\n<p>The problem is: I need to update it on the fly while the program\nis running (adding/removing some buttons) and the only way I found\nto do this, is to re-update the toolbar calling \"setToolbar\"\nagain.</p>\n<p>This works fine if my main view is at 0,0. If I have a view\nlarger than screen height, and I scroll it with my finger at Y &gt;\n0, when I call setToolbar I can see a very bad \"refresh\" problem\n(like toolbar is resized or it falls quickly from top).</p>\n<p>I hope I explained it well, btw it's very easy to reproduce\n:)</p>\n<p>There's a way to avoid that or something we could fix in the\nsource code??</p>\n<p>Thanks again.</p></div>{html}",
